Let us generalize this following Corollary~\ref{cor:generalsurg}. 
Let $K_m$ be a knot obtained from $K$ by $m$--twist along $C$.  
Then Corollary~\ref{cor:generalsurg} asserts that  
$K_m(n+m) \cong k_n(m+n)$ for any integers $m, n$.
Figure~\ref{fig:kcfamilies} demonstrates this fact pictorially. 


